
Selector, Node Afinity and Anti Afinity, POD Afinity and POD Anti Afinity:
--------------------------------------------------------------------------

Node Selector:
--------------

Means you have to mention where you need to run your deployment. you have to provide anyone server like SSD/OS/Tag etc.

Add lebel on worker node.


	> kubectl label nodes <node-name> disktype=ssd
	> kubectl label nodes <node-name> app=prod


Node Afinity:
-------------
Means you have to mention you want to run app anywhere. It will match the affinity rule.

kubectl label nodes <node-name-1> disktype=ssd
kubectl label nodes <node-name-2> disktype=hdd


Node Anti Afinity:
------------------

Means you have to mention where exactly you want to run exeept all node.

kubectl label nodes <node-name-1> zone=us-west
kubectl label nodes <node-name-2> zone=us-east